4
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:30,377
<i>a period known as
sede vacante:</i>

5
00:02:30,545 --> 00:02:33,131
<i>The time of the empty throne.</i>

6
00:02:35,342 --> 00:02:36,926
<i>Over the last several days</i>

7
00:02:37,094 --> 00:02:40,096
<i>Catholic leaders from every corner
of the world</i>

8
00:02:40,264 --> 00:02:43,982
<i>have flocked to Rome
shocked by the sudden death</i>

9
00:02:44,018 --> 00:02:47,395
<i>of this progressive
and beloved pope.</i>

10
00:02:54,194 --> 00:02:56,612
<i>Today, in St. Peter's Square</i>

11
00:02:56,780 --> 00:02:59,198
<i>the faithful pray
that there is among them</i>

12
00:02:59,366 --> 00:03:01,909
<i>another leader
who can unite their Church</i>

13
00:03:02,077 --> 00:03:06,038
<i>which has been so riven by change
and dissent in recent years.</i>

14
00:03:10,211 --> 00:03:12,963
<i>As the body of the pontiff
passes by</i>

15
00:03:13,131 --> 00:03:16,425
<i>we see prayers are being offered
by the preferiti</i>

16
00:03:16,593 --> 00:03:18,802
<i>favorites among those
being considered</i>

17
00:03:18,970 --> 00:03:22,890
<i>to succeed him
as the Vicar of Christ.</i>

18
00:03:32,192 --> 00:03:35,277
<i>At the end of the mourning period,
the College of Cardinals</i>

19
00:03:35,445 --> 00:03:39,907
<i>will lock itself behind the doors
of the Sistine Chapel for conclave</i>

20
00:03:40,074 --> 00:03:43,327
<i>the process by which they
will choose a new leader...</i>

21
00:03:43,495 --> 00:03:46,121
<i>for the world's
one billion Catholics</i>

22
00:03:46,289 --> 00:03:49,083
<i>who now find their Church
at a crossroads</i>

23
00:03:49,251 --> 00:03:53,171
<i>its ancient traditions threatened
by a modern world.</i>

24
