00:06:00,552 --> 00:06:02,678
Inject particle beams.

64
00:06:04,056 --> 00:06:05,556
Filling the LHC.

65
00:06:07,559 --> 00:06:10,061
Collisions are active.
We should be back online.

66
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:13,064
Capture should begin
at any moment.

67
00:06:13,232 --> 00:06:15,691
Particles in transition.

68
00:06:18,071 --> 00:06:22,241
Collisions are fixed and running.

69
00:06:22,408 --> 00:06:25,661
LHC injecting protons,
beam one.

70
00:06:28,248 --> 00:06:29,915
Lock the feedback systems.

71
00:06:30,083 --> 00:06:33,752
Particles at 99 percent
the speed of light.

72
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,963
Colliding stable beams.

73
00:06:36,631 --> 00:06:38,632
Enact injection kicker.

74
00:06:41,094 --> 00:06:43,971
We have a signal
on the luminosity monitors.

75
00:06:44,139 --> 00:06:46,265
We have events.

76
00:06:51,896 --> 00:06:53,647
Protons are moving.

77
00:07:13,252 --> 00:07:16,254
We have antimatter.

78
00:07:19,967 --> 00:07:23,803
It's on a scale never seen before.

79
00:07:24,305 --> 00:07:26,890
That's a crate of beer on the way.

80
00:07:31,103 --> 00:07:34,273
Silvano we've done it.

81
00:07:39,821 --> 00:07:43,657
We're in God's hands now, Vittoria.

82
00:07:44,326 --> 00:07:46,619
I'll be right down.

83
00:08:46,305 --> 00:08:49,725
Silvano.

84
00:09:12,416 --> 00:09:14,709
Oh, God.

85
00:09:15,294 --> 00:09:17,003
Help!

86
00:10:18,275 --> 00:10:21,152
A swim might help
your jet lag.

87
00:10:21,737 --> 00:10:22,987
I beg your pardon?

88
00:10:23,155 --> 00:10:26,116
You got bags under your eyes.
It's 5 in the morning.

89
00:10:26,283 --> 00:10:28,076
And you're from the Vatican.

90
00:10:29,829 --> 00:10:31,412
Crossed keys under the triregnum.

91
00:10:32,123 --> 00:10:33,915
It's a papal symbol.

92
00:10:36,961 --> 00:10:40,589
Claudio Vincenzi,
Corpo della Gendarmeria Vaticano.

93
00:10:41,508 --> 00:10:43,134
Vatican police?

94
00:10:44,761 --> 00:10:46,512
I was expecting another letter.

95
00:10:48,598 --> 00:10:51,767
My request for access
to your archives.

96
00:10:52,435 --> 00:10:54,103
Shouldn't you be in Rome?

97
00:10:54,271 --> 00:10:56,313
A kind of busy time for you guys,
isn't it?

98
00:10:56,481 --> 00:10:59,608
In fact, I was in New York,
detailed to the U.N.

99
00:10:59,776 --> 00:11:02,027
I receive a phone call
in the middle of the night:

100
00:11:02,195 --> 00:11:04,697
"Find Professor Robert Langdon.

101
00:11:04,865 --> 00:11:07,533
A matter of great urgency."

102
00:11:07,701 --> 00:11:11,787
They said to show you this.

103
00:11:24,218 --> 00:11:27,053
The Illuminati? They disappeared
hundreds of years ago.

104
00:11:27,221 --> 00:11:28,889
Did they? Look at that again.

105
00:11:29,056 --> 00:11:30,140
It's an ambigram.

106
00:11:30,308 --> 00:11:32,392
It's the same image
forward and backward.

107
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:35,729
Now, that's common for a symbol,
like a yin and yang or a swastika...

108
00:11:35,897 --> 00:11:37,147
but that's a word.

109
00:11:37,315 --> 00:11:39,232
That Illuminati
ambigramatic symbol...

110
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:42,235
has been considered a myth
for 400 years.

111
00:11:42,403 --> 00:11:44,029
Supposedly, in the 16th century

112
00:11:44,197 --> 00:11:48,200
some artist created it as a tribute
to Galileo's love of symmetry.

113
00:11:48,367 --> 00:11:49,826
It was only gonna be revealed

114
00:11:49,994 --> 00:11:52,245
when the Illuminati
had amassed enough power

115
00:11:52,413 --> 00:11:54,582
to resurface and carry out
their final goal.

116
00:11:54,792 --> 00:11:56,042
I wrote a book about it.

117
00:11:57,252 --> 00:11:58,586
Which is why you're here.

118
00:11:58,796 --> 00:12:00,922
The Art of the Illuminati
by Robert Langdon.

119
00:12:01,089 --> 00:12:02,423
Part one.

120
00:12:02,591 --> 00:12:05,551
Haven't been able to finish Part Two.
I'm not allowed access

121
00:12:05,719 --> 00:12:07,428
to your archives.

122
00:12:12,768 --> 00:12:15,269
It's remarkable. Singular.

123
00:12:15,437 --> 00:12:17,271
Someone is trying
to make you believe

124
00:12:17,439 --> 00:12:19,774
the Illuminati themselves
have returned to Rome.

125
00:12:19,942 --> 00:12:22,401
Right after the death of a pope.

126
00:12:26,156 --> 00:12:28,908
Four cardinals were kidnapped
from inside the Vatican

127
00:12:29,076 --> 00:12:31,995
sometime between 3 and 5 am.
This morning.

128
00:12:32,163 --> 00:12:33,872
Shortly afterward

129
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:36,959
that document was sent
to the office of the Swiss Guard

130
00:12:37,127 --> 00:12:40,754
along with the threat the cardinals
will be publicly executed...

131
00:12:40,922 --> 00:12:44,591
one per hour, beginning at 8 pm.
Tonight in Rome.

132
00:12:55,562 --> 00:12:57,563
- Conclave.
- Was to begin today.

133
00:12:57,730 --> 00:13:01,066
We've postponed its start
for a few hours, a story of illness.

134
00:13:01,234 --> 00:13:03,443
There are no suspicions yet.

135
00:13:04,571 --> 00:13:06,071
What do you want from me?

136
00:13:07,115 --> 00:13:10,577
These criminals
who sent this ambigram

137
00:13:10,744 --> 00:13:13,580
meant it as a taunt, a provocation.

138
00:13:13,747 --> 00:13:17,417
But Captain Olivetti think if you can
use it to learn their identity...

139
00:13:17,585 --> 00:13:20,670
perhaps we can stop
this abomination.

140
00:13:24,758 --> 00:13:26,134
Why me?

141
00:13:26,969 --> 00:13:29,929
Your expertise. Your erudition.

142
00:13:30,473 --> 00:13:34,767
Your recent involvement
with certain Church, shall we say

143
00:13:35,561 --> 00:13:36,644
mysteries.

144
00:13:37,521 --> 00:13:39,606
I wasn't under the impression
that episode

145
00:13:39,773 --> 00:13:41,774
had endeared me to the Vatican.

146
00:13:41,942 --> 00:13:43,151
Oh, it didn't.

147
00:13:43,611 --> 00:13:46,280
But it did make you...
What's the word?

148
00:13:46,448 --> 00:13:48,240
Formidabile.

149
00:13:49,201 --> 00:13:50,326
Formidable.

150
00:13:51,912 --> 00:13:54,455
A Vatican jet is standing by
20 minutes from here.

151
00:13:54,623 --> 00:13:55,790
Will you come with me?

152
00:14:04,132 --> 00:14:06,342
Professore Langdon,
you've spent your life

153
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:09,720
searching for symbols like the one
you now hold in your hand.

154
00:14:10,305 --> 00:14:12,181
How much longer are we
going to pretend

155
00:14:12,349 --> 00:14:14,683
you have not already
decided to come?

156
00:14:21,358 --> 00:14:24,528
If the Illuminati have returned
and are in Rome...

157
00:14:24,695 --> 00:14:27,823
we will hunt them down
and kill them.

158
00:14:28,991 --> 00:14:30,909
The Illuminati
did not become violent

159
00:14:31,077 --> 00:14:34,204
until the 17th century. Their name
means "the enlightened ones"

160
00:14:34,372 --> 00:14:37,374
They were physicists
and mathematicians, astronomers.

161
00:14:37,542 --> 00:14:40,418
They were concerned with
the Church's inaccurate teaching

162
00:14:40,586 --> 00:14:42,546
and were dedicated
to scientific truth.

163
00:14:42,713 --> 00:14:44,256
But the Vatican didn't like that.

164
00:14:44,423 --> 00:14:46,424
So the Church began to...
How did you say it?

165
00:14:46,592 --> 00:14:49,636
Oh, "hunt them down and kill them"

166
00:14:49,804 --> 00:14:51,388
Drove them underground.

167
00:14:52,849 --> 00:14:54,975
Into a secret society.

168
00:15:55,580 --> 00:15:57,414
Excuse me.

169
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:07,800
Comandante Richter assures me
the guard

170
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:11,386
is doing everything humanly possible
to find the preferiti.

171
00:16:11,554 --> 00:16:14,473
A long way to say very little.

172
00:16:15,851 --> 00:16:18,228
What if you were to begin
in their absence?

173
00:16:18,395 --> 00:16:20,146
They are the four leading candidates.

174
00:16:20,314 --> 00:16:22,482
If they're not present,
they're not eligible.

175
00:16:22,650 --> 00:16:27,946
There will be no consensus without
them. Who are we to vote for?

176
00:16:30,574 --> 00:16:35,161
It is as much a sin to offer flattery
as to accept it.

177
00:16:35,329 --> 00:16:38,122
May I suggest you at least consider
the possibility.

178
00:16:38,290 --> 00:16:39,958
No, no, no. There is no possibility.

179
00:16:40,126 --> 00:16:44,796
I have been chosen Great Elector.
I am not eligible.

180
00:16:48,050 --> 00:16:51,052
Camerlengo asks how long we can
postpone the opening prayer

181
00:16:51,220 --> 00:16:53,931
without making another
announcement to the public.

182
00:16:54,099 --> 00:16:58,644
Tell the camerlengo the cardinal-elect
will take every minute required

183
00:16:58,937 --> 00:17:02,064
to perform the sacred trust.

184
00:17:03,150 --> 00:17:05,734
No further announcements
are necessary.

185
00:17:07,529 --> 00:17:10,322
He'll be concerned
about the public dimension.

186
00:17:10,490 --> 00:17:14,118
- People will think...
- What we tell them to think.

187
00:17:18,206 --> 00:17:19,790
- Professor Langdon.
- Yes.

188
00:17:19,958 --> 00:17:21,834
Welcome to Vatican City.

189
00:17:22,711 --> 00:17:26,005
Ernesto Olivetti, inspector general
of the Vatican police force.

190
00:17:26,214 --> 00:17:28,174
- My pleasure.
- This way, please.

191
00:17:28,341 --> 00:17:31,011
We'll meet in the headquarters
of the Swiss Guard.

192
00:17:31,471 --> 00:17:33,346
I thought you were Swiss Guard.

193
00:17:33,514 --> 00:17:35,182
No, la Gendarmeria.

194
00:17:35,349 --> 00:17:38,935
We are responsible for everything
inside the Vatican walls

195
00:17:39,103 --> 00:17:42,522
with the exception
of the security of His Holiness...

196
00:17:42,690 --> 00:17:44,316
- Yeah.
- And the Apostolic Palace.

197
00:17:44,484 --> 00:17:46,026
That is Swiss Guard.

198
00:17:46,277 --> 00:17:49,905
The Roman carabinieri are here
as well in an advisory capacity.

199
00:17:50,072 --> 00:17:51,740
So jurisdictionally, this is.

200
00:17:51,908 --> 00:17:53,783
A goddamn nightmare.

201
00:18:00,625 --> 00:18:03,627
Oh, yes, Pope Pius IX's
great castration.

202
00:18:03,795 --> 00:18:06,755
- I beg your pardon?
- 1857, Pope Pius IX

203
00:18:06,923 --> 00:18:10,468
felt the male form
would inspire lust.

204
00:18:10,636 --> 00:18:12,136
So he took a hammer and chisel

205
00:18:12,304 --> 00:18:14,972
and unmanned hundreds
of these statues.

206
00:18:15,724 --> 00:18:19,060
The plaster fig leaves
were added later.

207
00:18:20,813 --> 00:18:24,732
Are you anti-Catholic,
Professor Langdon?

208
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:28,319
No. I'm anti-vandalism.

209
00:18:31,740 --> 00:18:34,450
I urge you to guard your tone here.

210
00:18:34,827 --> 00:18:38,704
The Swiss Guard is a calling,
not a profession

211
00:18:38,872 --> 00:18:43,668
and it encourages
a certain zealotry.

212
00:18:43,836 --> 00:18:45,796
Commander Richter,
the head of the Guard

213
00:18:45,964 --> 00:18:47,631
is a deeply spiritual man

214
00:18:47,799 --> 00:18:50,342
and he was close
to the late pope. Understood?

215
00:18:50,510 --> 00:18:53,637
Look, I don't study symbols
because I consider them unimportant.

216
00:18:53,805 --> 00:18:56,140
Ceremony, traditions,
it's how we mark our lives.

217
00:18:56,307 --> 00:18:58,183
I just... I just hope I can help.

218
00:18:58,351 --> 00:18:59,977
So do I.

219
00:19:00,145 --> 00:19:02,563
You were my idea.

220
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:16,368
Wait here. Please.

221
00:19:18,746 --> 00:19:20,038
Commander?

222
00:19:20,206 --> 00:19:21,540
Commander Richter?

223
00:19:22,459 --> 00:19:24,085
Professor Langdon is here.

224
00:19:24,253 --> 00:19:27,046
Well, we have bigger problems
than that now.

225
00:19:29,508 --> 00:19:31,634
Dr. Vetra?

226
00:19:32,636 --> 00:19:35,555
I'm Commander Richter, comandante
principale of the Swiss Guard.

227
00:19:35,723 --> 00:19:37,015
Thank you for coming.

228
00:19:37,183 --> 00:19:38,725
Hello.

229
00:19:39,477 --> 00:19:41,227
- Professor Langdon.
- Yes.

230
00:19:41,395 --> 00:19:43,897
What a relief,
the symbologist is here.

231
00:19:44,064 --> 00:19:46,065
This way, please, Miss Vetra.

232
00:19:48,152 --> 00:19:49,819
The situation has changed.

233
00:19:49,987 --> 00:19:53,281
We received another threat
from the kidnapper.

234
00:19:53,449 --> 00:19:56,242
The canister was stolen from our lab
around noon yesterday.

235
00:19:56,410 --> 00:19:59,955
The intruder killed my research
partner, Silvano Bentivoglio

236
00:20:00,123 --> 00:20:03,417
and mutilated him
in order to bypass security.

237
00:20:03,585 --> 00:20:05,377
We use retinal scanners.

238
00:20:06,004 --> 00:20:08,047
They cut out his eye.

239
00:20:09,132 --> 00:20:11,592
Is that your stolen canister,
Miss Vetra?

240
00:20:12,552 --> 00:20:14,386
Where is that camera, Number 86?

241
00:20:14,554 --> 00:20:16,180
It's wireless.
It too was stolen.

242
00:20:16,348 --> 00:20:18,182
It could be anywhere
inside the Vatican.

243
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:21,435
That canister contains
an extremely combustible substance.

244
00:20:21,603 --> 00:20:24,480
We need to locate it immediately
or evacuate Vatican City.

245
00:20:24,648 --> 00:20:27,149
I'm quite familiar
with incendiaries, Miss Vetra.

246
00:20:27,317 --> 00:20:29,610
I've never heard of antimatter
being used as such.

247
00:20:29,778 --> 00:20:32,780
Well, it's never been generated
in significant quantities before.

248
00:20:32,948 --> 00:20:35,658
It's a way of studying the origins
of the universe...

249
00:20:35,826 --> 00:20:38,703
to try to isolate what some people
call "the God particle"

250
00:20:38,871 --> 00:20:41,081
But there are implications
for energy research...

251
00:20:41,249 --> 00:20:43,124
"The God particle"?

252
00:20:44,126 --> 00:20:45,961
What we call it isn't important.

253
00:20:46,128 --> 00:20:47,796
It's what gives all matter mass.

254
00:20:47,964 --> 00:20:49,923
The thing without which
we could not exist.

255
00:20:50,091 --> 00:20:52,801
You're talking about
the moment of creation.

256
00:20:52,969 --> 00:20:54,594
Yes. In a way, I am.

257
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:57,722
The antimatter is suspended there...

258
00:20:57,890 --> 00:21:01,476
in an airtight nanocomposite shell
with electromagnets in each end.

259
00:21:01,644 --> 00:21:04,938
If it were to fall out of suspension
and come in contact with matter...

260
00:21:05,106 --> 00:21:07,983
say, the bottom of the canister,
the two opposing forces

261
00:21:08,151 --> 00:21:10,235
would annihilate one another
violently.

262
00:21:10,403 --> 00:21:12,696
And what might cause it
to fall out of suspension?

263
00:21:12,864 --> 00:21:14,282
The battery going dead.

264
00:21:14,449 --> 00:21:17,785
- Which it will, just before midnight.
- What kind of annihilation?

265
00:21:17,953 --> 00:21:20,663
- How violent?
- A cataclysmic event.

266
00:21:21,123 --> 00:21:25,334
A blinding explosion equivalent
to about five kilotons.

267
00:21:25,836 --> 00:21:29,505
Vatican City
will be consumed by light.

268
00:21:31,258 --> 00:21:33,968
Those are the exact words
the kidnapper used.

269
00:21:34,136 --> 00:21:37,555
We will destroy your four pillars.

270
00:21:38,348 --> 00:21:40,391
We will brand your preferiti

271
00:21:40,559 --> 00:21:43,895
and sacrifice them
on the altars of science

272
00:21:44,062 --> 00:21:47,023
then bring your church down
upon you.

273
00:21:47,191 --> 00:21:50,693
Vatican City
will be consumed by light.

274
00:21:50,861 --> 00:21:55,032
A shining star at the end
of the Path of Illumination.

275
00:22:00,788 --> 00:22:02,581
It's the ancient Illuminati threat.

276
00:22:02,749 --> 00:22:05,542
Destruction of Vatican City
through light.

277
00:22:05,919 --> 00:22:09,421
Four pillars,
there's your kidnapped cardinals.

278
00:22:09,589 --> 00:22:12,424
You didn't tell me they
were the preferiti, the favorites

279
00:22:12,592 --> 00:22:14,384
to be named the next pope.

280
00:22:16,763 --> 00:22:18,764
Play it again.

281
00:22:25,396 --> 00:22:27,981
We will destroy your four pillars.

282
00:22:29,902 --> 00:22:31,361
We will brand your preferiti...

283
00:22:31,529 --> 00:22:33,738
Wait, stop it. Stop it.

284
00:22:34,949 --> 00:22:37,200
"Brand" them.

285
00:22:38,911 --> 00:22:41,371
That's another Illuminati legend.

286
00:22:41,539 --> 00:22:46,918
This one says
that there are a set of five brands

287
00:22:47,086 --> 00:22:48,294
each one an ambigram.

288
00:22:48,462 --> 00:22:51,005
The first four are the fundamental
elements of science:

289
00:22:51,173 --> 00:22:53,258
Earth, air, fire and water.

290
00:22:53,425 --> 00:22:55,927
The fifth, it's a mystery.

291
00:22:58,013 --> 00:23:00,098
Maybe it's this.

292
00:23:00,766 --> 00:23:02,392
He said they'd be killed publicly.

293
00:23:03,018 --> 00:23:04,102
Yes.

294
00:23:04,645 --> 00:23:07,106
Revenge for la purga.

295
00:23:07,774 --> 00:23:08,899
"La purga"?

296
00:23:10,527 --> 00:23:13,904
Oh, jeez, you guys don't even read
your own history, do you?

297
00:23:14,072 --> 00:23:19,076
1668, the Church kidnapped
four Illuminati scientists

298
00:23:19,244 --> 00:23:21,370
and branded each one of them
on the chest

299
00:23:21,538 --> 00:23:23,455
with the symbol of the cross

300
00:23:23,623 --> 00:23:26,208
to purge them of their sins,
and they executed them.

301
00:23:26,376 --> 00:23:28,627
Threw their bodies into the street
as a warning

302
00:23:28,795 --> 00:23:32,423
to others to stop questioning
Church rulings on scientific matters.

303
00:23:32,591 --> 00:23:33,632
They radicalized them.

304
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:36,760
The purga created a darker,
more violent Illuminati

305
00:23:36,928 --> 00:23:39,472
one bent on retribution.

306
00:23:40,307 --> 00:23:42,057
Look how they intend
to finally get it:

307
00:23:42,225 --> 00:23:45,645
Using antimatter, technology,
to destroy the Church.

308
00:23:45,813 --> 00:23:48,106
Science obliterates religion.

309
00:23:49,525 --> 00:23:51,109
Is there any more?

310
00:23:52,653 --> 00:23:56,031
- And sacrifice them
on the altars of science

311
00:23:56,199 --> 00:23:59,075
then bring your church down
upon you.

312
00:23:59,243 --> 00:24:02,704
Vatican City will be consumed
by light.

313
00:24:02,872 --> 00:24:07,125
A shining star at the end
of the Path of Illumination.

314
00:24:07,293 --> 00:24:09,419
"Path of Illumination"

315
00:24:12,548 --> 00:24:14,758
I need access
to the Vatican archives.

316
00:24:16,844 --> 00:24:19,304
Professor, I don't think
this is the appropriate...

317
00:24:19,472 --> 00:24:21,349
Your petition has been denied
seven times.

318
00:24:21,517 --> 00:24:25,019
No, no. This has nothing to do with
my work. The Path of Illumination

319
00:24:25,187 --> 00:24:28,022
is a trail that leads
to the Church of the Illumination

320
00:24:28,190 --> 00:24:31,275
the place where the Illuminati
would meet in secret.

321
00:24:31,443 --> 00:24:33,694
If I can find the segno, the sign

322
00:24:34,488 --> 00:24:38,491
that marks the beginning of that
path, the four churches along it

323
00:24:38,659 --> 00:24:41,410
may be where he intends
to murder your cardinals.

324
00:24:41,578 --> 00:24:44,372
One every hour at 8, 9, 10 and 11.

325
00:24:44,540 --> 00:24:47,208
Then the device explodes
at midnight.

326
00:24:47,876 --> 00:24:51,087
If we can figure out the first church
and get there before he does

327
00:24:51,255 --> 00:24:54,382
maybe we can stop it.
But I can't find the start of the path

328
00:24:54,550 --> 00:24:56,467
until I get into the archives.

329
00:24:57,427 --> 00:24:59,137
Even if I wanted to help you

330
00:24:59,305 --> 00:25:01,807
access to the archives
is only by written decree

331
00:25:01,975 --> 00:25:04,852
by the curator
and the Board of Vatican Librarians.

332
00:25:05,019 --> 00:25:06,687
Or by papal mandate.

333
00:25:06,855 --> 00:25:10,691
Yes, but as you no doubt have heard,
the Holy Father is dead.

334
00:25:11,526 --> 00:25:12,818
What about il camerlengo?

335
00:25:12,986 --> 00:25:16,321
The camerlengo is just a priest here,
the former pope's chamberlain.

336
00:25:16,489 --> 00:25:20,492
Doesn't the power of the Holy See rest
in him during tempe sede vacante?

337
00:25:28,459 --> 00:25:31,336
Fellas, you called me.

338
00:25:32,755 --> 00:25:34,423
His Holiness once told me a pope

339
00:25:34,591 --> 00:25:38,219
was a man torn between
the real world and the divine.

340
00:25:38,387 --> 00:25:41,556
It seems the real world
is upon us tonight.

341
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:46,227
I'm familiar with Illuminati lore
and the legend of the brandings.

342
00:25:46,645 --> 00:25:49,939
La purga is a dark stain
on this Church's history.

343
00:25:50,107 --> 00:25:53,151
I'm not surprised this ghost
has returned to haunt us.

344
00:25:55,362 --> 00:25:58,740
Comandante, have you begun
the search for this explosive device?

345
00:25:58,908 --> 00:26:00,617
Of course, but it could be anywhere.

346
00:26:00,784 --> 00:26:03,703
My primary concern at the moment
is the safety of the cardinals.

347
00:26:03,871 --> 00:26:05,872
The Sistine Chapel is a fortress.

348
00:26:06,040 --> 00:26:08,750
As long as the cardinals
are in conclave, your concerns

349
00:26:08,918 --> 00:26:11,461
are at a minimum.
Devote as many of your resources...

350
00:26:11,629 --> 00:26:13,839
If you're about to suggest
a naked-eye search

351
00:26:14,007 --> 00:26:17,384
of the entire Vatican City, I will tell
you we do not have the people.

352
00:26:17,552 --> 00:26:20,554
Though I am not His Holiness,
when you are addressing me

353
00:26:20,722 --> 00:26:23,140
you are addressing this oftice.
Do you understand?

354
00:26:25,435 --> 00:26:26,477
Yes, Father.

355
00:26:27,062 --> 00:26:28,813
Good.

356
00:26:29,648 --> 00:26:33,734
You said the image on the screen
was illuminated by artificial light.

357
00:26:33,902 --> 00:26:36,028
Might I suggest
methodically cutting power

358
00:26:36,196 --> 00:26:38,322
to various sections of the city.

359
00:26:38,490 --> 00:26:41,075
When the image goes dark,
you'll have a specific idea

360
00:26:41,243 --> 00:26:43,327
of the camera's location.

361
00:26:46,748 --> 00:26:50,209
Dr. Vetra, besides yourself
and your research partner

362
00:26:50,377 --> 00:26:53,797
who else knew
about this antimatter project?

363
00:26:54,215 --> 00:26:58,593
No one but the research team.
This project was strictly confidential.

364
00:26:58,761 --> 00:27:00,679
But Silvano kept detailed journals.

365
00:27:00,847 --> 00:27:02,138
If he told anyone else

366
00:27:02,723 --> 00:27:05,267
about what we were doing,
he would have made a note.

367
00:27:05,434 --> 00:27:06,852
Do you have these journals?

368
00:27:07,019 --> 00:27:09,563
I can have them flown here
from Geneva in an hour.

369
00:27:09,730 --> 00:27:11,398
Please.

370
00:27:12,775 --> 00:27:14,109
Professor Langdon.

371
00:27:25,288 --> 00:27:30,918
Mr. Langdon, you are correct that I
may grant you access to the archives.

372
00:27:33,046 --> 00:27:34,797
Thank you, Padre.

373
00:27:34,965 --> 00:27:38,718
I said that you were correct
that I may, not that I will.

374
00:27:39,887 --> 00:27:42,889
Christianity's most sacred codices
are in that archive.

375
00:27:44,391 --> 00:27:47,810
Given your recent entanglement
with the Church

376
00:27:47,978 --> 00:27:50,313
there is a question I'd like
to ask you first

377
00:27:50,481 --> 00:27:52,940
in the office of His Holiness.

378
00:28:00,741 --> 00:28:02,408
Do you believe in God, sir?

379
00:28:06,206 --> 00:28:09,583
Father, I simply believe
that religion...

380
00:28:09,751 --> 00:28:13,253
I did not ask if you believe
what man says about God.

381
00:28:13,421 --> 00:28:15,255
I asked if you believe in God.

382
00:28:18,218 --> 00:28:19,927
I'm an academic.

383
00:28:21,054 --> 00:28:24,014
My mind tells me I will never

384
00:28:24,265 --> 00:28:25,724
understand God.

385
00:28:26,768 --> 00:28:28,352
And your heart?

386
00:28:31,189 --> 00:28:33,482
Tells me I'm not meant to.

387
00:28:34,943 --> 00:28:36,527
Faith is a gift

388
00:28:36,778 --> 00:28:38,946
that I have yet to receive.

389
00:28:45,454 --> 00:28:48,039
Be delicate with our treasures.

390
00:28:54,463 --> 00:28:55,630
The archives are this way.

391
00:28:55,798 --> 00:28:57,715
Professor Langdon.

392
00:28:58,801 --> 00:29:01,970
If this path really leads
to the Church of Illumination

393
00:29:02,137 --> 00:29:04,472
that may be where they've hidden
the antimatter.

394
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:06,432
"A shining star
at the end of the path."

395
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:07,642
Follow the path.

396
00:29:07,810 --> 00:29:10,645
- We may find the canister.
- Can you deactivate the device?

397
00:29:10,813 --> 00:29:12,147
I can change the batteries

398
00:29:12,314 --> 00:29:14,566
as long as we have
more than five minutes.

399
00:29:14,733 --> 00:29:17,986
That would give us another 24 hours
to get it safely back to CERN.

400
00:29:21,074 --> 00:29:22,116
Robert Langdon.

401
00:29:22,284 --> 00:29:23,951
Vittoria Vetra.

402
00:29:24,119 --> 00:29:27,621
Are you really a symbologist,
or was he mocking you?

403
00:29:27,789 --> 00:29:29,957
Well, both. You're a physicist?

404
00:29:30,125 --> 00:29:33,335
Bio-entanglement physics.
Interconnectivity of life systems.

405
00:29:33,503 --> 00:29:34,795
Okay.

406
00:29:34,963 --> 00:29:38,007
Your project, it was geared
towards energy research?

407
00:29:38,175 --> 00:29:39,341
Eventually, yes.

408
00:29:39,509 --> 00:29:43,512
One speck of antimatter
could power an entire city for a month.

409
00:29:43,763 --> 00:29:46,098
Or tonight, I guess, destroy one.

410
00:29:47,309 --> 00:29:49,143
What are we looking for
in the archives?

411
00:29:49,311 --> 00:29:51,020
A bound volume written by Galileo.

412
00:29:51,188 --> 00:29:52,813
Galileo was Illuminati?

413
00:29:52,981 --> 00:29:55,691
Yeah. And an obedient Catholic
who didn't think

414
00:29:55,859 --> 00:29:57,736
that Church and science
were enemies

415
00:29:57,904 --> 00:30:00,238
but a different language
telling the same story.

416
00:30:00,406 --> 00:30:03,074
He wanted like minds
to find the Church of Illumination...

417
00:30:03,242 --> 00:30:08,497
but he couldn't exactly advertise its
location so he created a coded path.

418
00:30:09,207 --> 00:30:11,875
Richter has started to turn off
the power of various grids.

419
00:30:12,043 --> 00:30:14,169
It'll be back on in a minute.

420
00:30:14,712 --> 00:30:18,381
Then some unknown Illuminati master
sculpted four statues.

421
00:30:18,925 --> 00:30:21,593
Each one a tribute to one
of the fundamental elements

422
00:30:21,761 --> 00:30:23,512
earth, air, fire, water

423
00:30:23,679 --> 00:30:27,140
and placed the statues out in public
in churches throughout Rome.

424
00:30:27,308 --> 00:30:29,893
Each statue held a clue
pointing to the next.

425
00:30:30,061 --> 00:30:32,562
At the end of the path
was the Church of Illumination.

426
00:30:32,730 --> 00:30:35,691
If you could find that,
you were one of them.

427
00:30:35,859 --> 00:30:38,611
What makes you think he's going
to murder in the churches?

428
00:30:39,112 --> 00:30:41,113
The Illuminati called
those four churches

429
00:30:41,281 --> 00:30:45,117
by the special name,
L'Altare della scienza.

430
00:30:45,285 --> 00:30:48,246
"Sacrifice them on the altars
of science,", he said.

431
00:30:48,413 --> 00:30:50,081
Exactly.

432
00:30:53,252 --> 00:30:56,170
Oh, wow. Look at this.

433
00:31:21,531 --> 00:31:23,782
Excuse me, signore.

434
00:31:25,201 --> 00:31:27,995
Cardinal Strauss,
you've been informed of the situation?

435
00:31:28,163 --> 00:31:29,621
Yeah.

436
00:31:30,081 --> 00:31:33,667
My belief is we should proceed
with the sealing of conclave.

437
00:31:33,835 --> 00:31:37,629
At this late hour?
That would be highly unorthodox.

438
00:31:37,797 --> 00:31:41,258
And yet within Church law.
It's in my power. I am Great Elector.

439
00:31:41,426 --> 00:31:43,594
The cruelest honor in Christendom.

440
00:31:43,761 --> 00:31:47,139
I have no personal ambitions,
Patrick.

441
00:31:47,307 --> 00:31:51,144
Only those I hold for my Church,
St. Peter's Church...

442
00:31:51,312 --> 00:31:54,147
which is under attack
at its most vulnerable moment.

443
00:31:54,315 --> 00:31:55,732
And this is not a coincidence.

444
00:31:55,900 --> 00:31:59,319
The Church will not fall in a day.
We must evacuate Vatican City.

445
00:31:59,487 --> 00:32:02,405
Oh, that is exactly what they want.

446
00:32:02,573 --> 00:32:04,240
Publicity and panic.

447
00:32:04,408 --> 00:32:07,410
No, we must not give them oxygen
for the media fire.

448
00:32:08,454 --> 00:32:10,663
But the people
in St. Peter's Square...

449
00:32:10,831 --> 00:32:15,001
Care deeply about their Church,
as we do.

450
00:32:15,169 --> 00:32:17,587
Their faith will sustain them.

451
00:32:17,755 --> 00:32:20,256
Their faith will not protect them
from an explosion.

452
00:32:20,424 --> 00:32:21,966
Well.

453
00:32:22,134 --> 00:32:26,638
We are all bound for heaven
eventually, are we not?

454
00:32:26,805 --> 00:32:30,184
Spoken like one who has enjoyed
the blessings of a long and full life.

455
00:32:30,352 --> 00:32:31,852
Patrick

456
00:32:32,020 --> 00:32:35,272
do not confuse the power
of the office you temporarily hold

457
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:38,359
with your true place
here in the Vatican.

458
00:32:40,195 --> 00:32:42,696
You were a favorite
of His Holiness

459
00:32:43,198 --> 00:32:46,700
but His Holiness
is with his father now.

460
00:32:49,204 --> 00:32:50,496
Mea culpa.

461
00:32:51,206 --> 00:32:52,915
Seal the doors.

462
00:33:07,473 --> 00:33:09,891
Extra omnes.

463
00:34:27,847 --> 00:34:30,098
Hello. This way, please.

464
00:34:31,309 --> 00:34:32,809
Oh, beautiful.

465
00:34:37,732 --> 00:34:39,441
The chambers are hermetic vaults.

466
00:34:39,609 --> 00:34:41,777
Oxygen is kept
at lowest possible levels.

467
00:34:41,945 --> 00:34:43,821
It's a partial vacuum inside.

468
00:34:43,988 --> 00:34:46,490
So extended stays
are not recommended.

469
00:34:47,116 --> 00:34:50,285
So don't panic if you feel
lightheaded at first.

470
00:35:02,299 --> 00:35:04,050
I'll be just outside the door.

471
00:35:04,552 --> 00:35:06,886
Watching you, Mr. Langdon.

472
00:35:23,654 --> 00:35:26,156
By the way,
it's normal to feel a little light-headed.

473
00:35:26,323 --> 00:35:31,244
Yeah. Feels like I'm scuba diving
with the wrong mixture.

474
00:35:31,412 --> 00:35:33,246
Take a second. We have time.

475
00:35:35,041 --> 00:35:36,959
Actually, I take that back.

476
00:35:37,127 --> 00:35:40,921
- Is that Mickey Mouse?
- Yeah. It's a long story.

477
00:36:32,767 --> 00:36:35,435
Conclave will go on without us.

478
00:36:35,603 --> 00:36:39,523
It must, now of all times.

479
00:36:39,690 --> 00:36:42,400
May God forgive you
for what you've done.

480
00:36:50,410 --> 00:36:52,203
Father, if God has issues

481
00:36:53,330 --> 00:36:56,457
they won't be with what I've done.

482
00:36:56,625 --> 00:36:59,418
They will be
with what I'm about to do.

483
00:37:20,983 --> 00:37:23,234
It was confiscated
from the Netherlands

484
00:37:23,402 --> 00:37:26,488
by the Vatican
just after Galileo died.

485
00:37:26,656 --> 00:37:29,116
I've been petitioning to see it
for about 10 years

486
00:37:29,284 --> 00:37:31,910
ever since I realized
what was in it.

487
00:37:32,078 --> 00:37:33,996
What makes you so sure
the segno's there?

488
00:37:34,164 --> 00:37:35,539
The number 503.

489
00:37:35,707 --> 00:37:39,710
I kept seeing it over and over again
in Illuminati letters

490
00:37:39,878 --> 00:37:43,672
scribbled in the margins,
sometimes just signed "503."

491
00:37:43,840 --> 00:37:45,507
It's a numeric clue. But to what?

492
00:37:45,675 --> 00:37:48,594
Five? Well, that's a meaningful
number to the Illuminati.

493
00:37:48,761 --> 00:37:52,055
There's the pentagram, Pythagoras,
dozens of other examples in science.

494
00:37:52,223 --> 00:37:53,265
But what about three?

495
00:37:53,433 --> 00:37:56,602
Didn't make sense until I thought,
"What if it's Roman numerals?"

496
00:37:56,769 --> 00:38:00,647
- D-III.
- D-three. Galileo's third text.

